For web developers, firefox made another awesome feature for responsive web development. The Touch simulator using the mouse and Screenshots.

# Responsive Design View
When responsive web design gets popular, Mozilla Firefox launched a tool for develop websites simulating different devices resolutions helping developers to build responsive web sites without a gadget(Smartphone, Tablets, etc...).
<br />
# The New Firefox Feature!
Upgrading to Firefox 26.0 you can open the Responsive Design View and check out for two new buttons:<br />
### - Simulate Touch Events
This feature will simulate your mouse like a finger in the page. When you click something is going to simulate your touch in a button. Its a pretty experience but its a beginning.
<br />
### - Screenshot
The simulator is not 100%. But you can show your responsive web site to everybody taking screenshots of it.
<br /><br />
